</gallery>

=== Transportation ===
{{osm box|n|1229000716|Oba Shrine (Inari, Fujisawa City)}}
* From {{ill|lt=Fujisawa Station|Q1133110|WD=Q1133110|1=Fujisawa Station}} North Exit/{{ill|lt=Shonandai Station|Q1036357|WD=Q1036357|1=Shōnandai Station}} West Exit {{ill|lt=Kanagawa Chuo Kotsu|Q10854960|WD=Q10854960|lt=Kanachu Bus|1=Kanagawa Chuo Kotsu}}{{ill|lt=Kanagawa Chuo Kotsu Fujisawa Office #Fujisawa Station North Exit - Ishikawa Bridge - Isshikigami - From the west exit of Shonandai Station|Q11588895|WD=Q11588895|lt=Fuji 34|1=Fuji 34}}, or from the west exit of Zengyo Station, take the Kanachu bus {{ill|lt=Kanagawa Chuo Kotsu Fujisawa Office #Zengyo Station - Wholesale Market Front|Q11588895|WD=Q11588895|lt=Zen 03|1=Zen 03}}, get off at Tenjinsha-mae, and walk 6 minutes to Ichi-no-Torii.
* About 25 minutes walk from Odakyu Line {{ill|lt=Zengyo Station|Q4160904|WD=Q4160904|1=Zengyō Station}}.

=== A work set at Oba Shrine ===
* {{ill|lt=Futatsu no Spica|Q2511557|WD=Q2511557|1=Twin Spica}} - In {{ill|lt=2009|Q1996|WD=Q1996|1=2009}}, location shooting for the TV drama version that was broadcast in the "{{ill|lt=Drama 8|Q11323102|WD=Q11323102|1=Drama 8}}" slot of {{ill|lt=NHK General Television|Q909336|WD=Q909336|lt=NHK General Television|1=NHK General TV}} was held<ref>{{Cite web|Japanese book|author= |date= |url=http://www.city.fujisawa.kanagawa.jp/kouhou/khf100310/sisei02.html |title=Enriching the region through location support! ~Shonan Fujisawa Film Commission |publisher=Fujisawa City |accessdate=2018-11-10}}</ref>.

