File:OOBA-Jinjya-kuma05.JPG|<center>Rotten information board</center>
</gallery>

=== Transportation ===
* Take the Kanachu Bus Fuji 34 from the north exit of Fujisawa Station or the west exit of Shonandai Station, or the Kanachu Bus Zen 03 from the west exit of Yoshiyuki Station, get off at "Benten-mae" and walk 6 minutes.

=== External link ===
* [http://www.kanagawa-jinja.or.jp/search_dtl.php4?jid=545&cd=1206026&scd=&npg=0 Kumano Shrine] (Kanagawa Prefectural Shrine Agency)

=== Notes ===
Currently, {{ill|lt=Kodai Jingu (Fujisawa City)|Q11675783|WD=Q11675783|lt=Kodai Jingu|1=Kōdai-jingū}} is in charge of managing both shrines, so you will need to get the {{ill|lt=Red seal (shrines and temples)|Q7504772|WD=Q7504772|lt=Goshuin|1=Shuin}} from there.

